By using FitBlaze, you agree to the terms of this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree, please do not use the App.
1. Information We Collect
We may collect the following types of information:
a) Personal Information
Name, email address, phone number, or other identifiers you provide when creating an account.
Login credentials (encrypted).
b) Health & Fitness Information
Workout details, activity tracking, calories, and other fitness data you choose to share.
HealthKit or Google Fit data (with your permission).
c) Device & Usage Information
Device type, operating system, and unique identifiers.
App usage statistics, crash reports, and log files.
d) Location Information
If you enable GPS features, we may collect your location data to provide activity tracking services.
2. How We Use Your Information
We use your information to:
Provide and improve our services.
Personalize workout recommendations and insights.
Sync with third-party health platforms (if enabled).
Communicate updates, offers, or important notices.
Ensure security, detect fraud, and comply with legal obligations.
3. Sharing of Information
We do not sell your personal information. We may share data only in these cases:
With service providers who help us operate the App (e.g., cloud storage, analytics).
With your consent when integrating with third-party apps (e.g., HealthKit, Google Fit).
For legal reasons if required by law, court order, or to protect rights and safety.
4. Data Storage & Security
Your data is stored securely on trusted servers.
We use encryption and industry-standard safeguards to protect information.
However, no system is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute protection.
5. Your Rights
Depending on your location, you may have rights to:
Access, update, or delete your personal data.
Withdraw consent for data processing.
Opt out of promotional communications.
To exercise these rights, contact us at support@fitblaze.com.
6. Children‚Äôs Privacy
FitBlaze is not directed to children under 16. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children. If we learn that a child has provided information, we will delete it promptly.
7. Third-Party Services
FitBlaze may link to or integrate with third-party platforms (e.g., Apple Health, Google Fit). Your use of those services is subject to their privacy policies, not ours.
8. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Updates will be posted in the App with a new effective date. Continued use of FitBlaze means you accept the changes.
